verbs.description: arrow (third-person singular simple present arrows, present participle arrowing, simple past and past participle arrowed)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To move swiftly and directly (like an arrow).
(transitive) To let fly swiftly and directly.
(intransitive, botany, of a sugar cane plant) To develop an inflorescence.
(computing, intransitive) To navigate using the arrow keys.
examples: Arrow left until you reach the start of the text you want to delete.
